<TEXT>     The panel also found that "agents of the Chilean state" were responsible
for the Sept. 21, 1976, car bombing in Washington that killed Orlando Letelier
-- formerly Allende's ambassador to the United States -- and his assistant
Ronnie Moffet.  </TEXT>
